🏔️ 1. heapq Module

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is heapq?

```text id="heapq_def"
heapq provides an implementation of the heap queue (priority queue) algorithm.
```

---

📌 Heap Property

```text id="heap_property"
Smallest element is always at the root.
```

---

📥 Import

```python id="heap_import"
import heapq
```

---

💻 Create Heap

```python id="heap_create"
import heapq

numbers = [4, 1, 7, 3]

heapq.heapify(numbers)

print(numbers)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="heap_output"
[1, 3, 7, 4]
```

---

➕ Insert Element

```python id="heap_push"
import heapq

heap = [1, 3, 5]

heapq.heappush(
    heap,
    2
)

print(heap)
```

---

❌ Remove Smallest Element

```python id="heap_pop"
import heapq

heap = [1, 3, 5]

print(
    heapq.heappop(heap)
)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="heap_pop_output"
1
```

---

🔍 Largest Elements

```python id="largest_heap"
import heapq

numbers = [10, 5, 30, 20]

print(
    heapq.nlargest(
        2,
        numbers
    )
)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="largest_output"
[30, 20]
```

---

🎯 Applications

✔ Task Scheduling
✔ Priority Queues
